<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>&gt; We today do not have the technology to go to Mars in<br>
any meaningful way; what is possible today is too slow, too<br>
small, and too dangerous to do anything beyond a half<br>
hearted attempt to look for bugs - in short, a Martial Apollo.</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
Again, I see that you don't seem to have read or understood &quot;the Case for Mars&quot;. If it's too small scale for you (only 4 people, but they have immense resources for exploration), then scale it up a bit to the (presumeably abandoned) NASA Baseline version, called Mars Semi-Direct.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>&gt; And why shouldn't the OSP program be &quot;stretched&quot; to<br>
go to the Moon? It takes two days to reach ISS, whats<br>
another day or two to get to Luna?</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
Completely different requirements. Wildly different conditions. Presumeably, this maneuver is intended to reduce costs by combining functions, but the design requirements are so different that so many totally different variants would be needed that there would be no commonality between them, so it's like re-inventing the wheel every time.<br>
<br>
 It should take maybe 8-12 hours to do most crew ferry functions. Double or triple this for reserve and orbital changes. It takes 5 days to get to the Moon, so there's another totally new piece of equipment to integrate in the life support and power conditioning. What about delta-V? A few hundred meters/sec for total mission requirements. Another different piece in the propulsion/services just to let the craft function and make the orbital maneuvers to get from LEO to Lunar injection, Lunar orbit capture, then break away to get back towards Earth, and then to get into a circular LEO.<br>
 What possible use are landing provisions for Earth on the Moon?<br>
The whole concept is as silly as taking the Space Shuttle to the Moon. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#333333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/bnuclearspace.showUserPublicProfile?gid=johnfraz>John Fraz</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Orion Commander</span><br>  Posts: 476<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(1/17/04 4:10 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=993.topic&index=26>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://lneilsmith.com/tools/littlelogo.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   The government money cannon</span><hr size=1>  Imperator (1/16/04)<br>
